  "prompt": "What is asset servicing?",
  "response": "Asset servicing is a financial service provided by banks, custodians, and other financial institutions to help investors manage and maintain their investment portfolios. It involves a range of administrative, operational, and support functions related to various types of assets, such as stocks, bonds, mutual funds, and other securities. Key aspects of asset servicing include:\n\n1. Record keeping and accounting\n- Tracking asset holdings\n- Monitoring transactions\n- Maintaining accurate financial records\n\n2. Corporate actions processing\n- Handling dividend payments\n- Managing stock splits\n- Processing mergers and acquisitions\n- Tracking bond interest payments\n\n3. Performance reporting\n- Generating periodic investment reports\n- Calculating investment returns\n- Providing portfolio performance analysis\n\n4. Securities settlement\n- Executing trades\n- Clearing transactions\n- Transferring securities and funds\n\n5. Compliance and regulatory reporting\n- Ensuring adherence to financial regulations\n- Preparing tax-related documentation\n- Maintaining regulatory compliance\n\n6. Cash management\n- Managing dividend and interest collections\n- Processing fund transfers\n- Maintaining cash balances\n\n7. Risk management\n- Monitoring investment risks\n- Providing risk assessment tools\n- Supporting portfolio diversification strategies\n\nAsset servicing helps investors and institutions efficiently manage their investment portfolios and optimize their financial operations.",
